        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 7 at 2:55PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 255 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Boardman, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boardman, Irrigon, Hermiston, and Paterson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
